The paper discusses statistical analysis of science and technical information (STI) in the Web context, which involves web usage analysis, bibliographic records, and e-commercial transactions. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Cybersecurity (cs.CY), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). However, since the focus is on web usage analysis and bibliographic records, cs.IR and cs.DL are the most likely sub-categories.
